    // If (a == 0 and d == 0), magnitude < 1 is guaranteed.
    // If (a > 0 or d > 0), we can choose values such that the product is < 1.
    // E.g., if we have a toy with value 2, and all others are 0.1.
    // We can multiply 2 with 0.1 to get 0.2. Then 0.2 with 0.1 to get 0.02.
